<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/6323> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #6323" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "See 42, Legates. In CIL 11.6058 a certain Marius calls himself Prefect in the fleet of Cn. Lentulus in Sicily. Groag favors the view that Lentulus was a Legatus pro praetore under Sextus Pompey (see 42, Legates), but he may have returned after 39 and become Praetor in 38 or some subsequent year." ;
	dprr:hasID 6323 .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/6183> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #6183" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "When proscribed, he escaped to Sextus Pompey in Sicily, who, according to Appian, made him a # (4.39; cf. Val. Max. 6.7.3). Perhaps a Legatus pro praetore, like Plinius Rufus; see CIL 11.6058; Groag, Klio 14 (1914) 51; PIR² 2.338, no. 1389." ;
	dprr:hasID 6183 .
